author: Suhas Nayse
title: Nagpur varsity shuttlers qualify for all India meet
text:
NAGPUR: Nagpur University men's and women's teams excelled at the West Zone Inter-University Badminton tournament being played at Gwalior on Wednesday. 

According to the reports reaching here, both the teams stormed into the semi-finals which paved way for their qualification for the forthcoming All India Inter-University meet. The top four teams of the West Zone qualify for the all India tournament. 

Vaishnavi Bhale, Bhakti Dahasahasra and Khushboo Patel performed well for the NU women's side. Gaurav Rege, Manan Goenka, Kunal Dasarwar and Akash Joshi did well for the NU men's team. Stay updated on the go with Times of India News App. Click here to download it for your device.
